00:16:54.380 --> 00:16:55.820 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:16:55.820 --> 00:17:00.530 align:middle line:84%
So what do you think about the
conventional recommendations

00:17:00.530 --> 00:17:01.790 align:middle line:90%
for back problems?

00:17:01.790 --> 00:17:04.579 align:middle line:84%
Obviously, it's not
this, but other things.

00:17:04.579 --> 00:17:09.329 align:middle line:84%
Examples, surgery, medicating,
rehabilitation in other ways.

00:17:09.329 --> 00:17:10.670 align:middle line:90%
What do you think about--

00:17:10.670 --> 00:17:13.790 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, sometimes like what
every parent tells their kids,

00:17:13.790 --> 00:17:17.119 align:middle line:84%
sit up straight, is
just plain wrong.

00:17:17.119 --> 00:17:18.859 align:middle line:90%
It's misguided.

00:17:18.859 --> 00:17:22.970 align:middle line:84%
Many, many of the interventions
out there are helpful,

00:17:22.970 --> 00:17:24.530 align:middle line:90%
but they deal with symptoms.

00:17:24.530 --> 00:17:28.550 align:middle line:84%
It's sort of a hack,
it's a Band-Aid.

00:17:28.550 --> 00:17:31.910 align:middle line:84%
Without understanding what's
at the root of the problem,

00:17:31.910 --> 00:17:36.100 align:middle line:84%
we can make the pain
disappear by doing pain meds

00:17:36.100 --> 00:17:38.450 align:middle line:90%
or by injecting or--

00:17:38.450 --> 00:17:43.040 align:middle line:84%
but I think it's really
important at some stage

00:17:43.040 --> 00:17:45.710 align:middle line:84%
in the game to address
the root of the problem.

00:17:45.710 --> 00:17:49.560 align:middle line:84%
The reason we have pain, that's
nature's way of saying, hey.

00:17:49.560 --> 00:17:51.440 align:middle line:90%
Something's not quite right.

00:17:51.440 --> 00:17:53.970 align:middle line:84%
And then we need to not
just kill the messenger

00:17:53.970 --> 00:17:55.470 align:middle line:90%
or ignore the messenger.

00:17:55.470 --> 00:17:59.250 align:middle line:84%
We need to understand the
messenger, do the necessary,

00:17:59.250 --> 00:18:00.050 align:middle line:90%
and move forward.

00:18:00.050 --> 00:18:00.850 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:18:00.850 --> 00:18:03.410 align:middle line:84%
What do you think about
the standard advice

00:18:03.410 --> 00:18:07.145 align:middle line:84%
that most physicians would
give us about staying active?

00:18:07.145 --> 00:18:09.920 align:middle line:84%
You have to stay active,
or in other situations

00:18:09.920 --> 00:18:12.575 align:middle line:84%
to completely lay in
bed until this heals.

00:18:12.575 --> 00:18:13.950 align:middle line:84%
What-- how do you
work with that?

00:18:13.950 --> 00:18:15.283 align:middle line:90%
How do you make those decisions?

00:18:15.283 --> 00:18:18.110 align:middle line:84%
>> So laying in
bed is old school.

00:18:18.110 --> 00:18:20.300 align:middle line:90%
That's no longer recommended.

00:18:20.300 --> 00:18:22.400 align:middle line:84%
And that's a good thing,
because it turns out

00:18:22.400 --> 00:18:24.050 align:middle line:90%
that's not very helpful.

00:18:24.050 --> 00:18:29.300 align:middle line:84%
Staying active, I think,
is a good piece of advice,

00:18:29.300 --> 00:18:32.066 align:middle line:84%
but it could be
done so much better.

00:18:32.066 --> 00:18:35.510 align:middle line:84%
Obviously, you have to
do what your body allows.

00:18:35.510 --> 00:18:37.340 align:middle line:84%
You have to tune
in, and sometimes

00:18:37.340 --> 00:18:39.710 align:middle line:84%
less active,
sometimes more active.

00:18:39.710 --> 00:18:43.490 align:middle line:84%
But a key thing
that's missing is

00:18:43.490 --> 00:18:45.020 align:middle line:90%
how are you going to be active?

00:18:45.020 --> 00:18:46.920 align:middle line:90%
What is the shape of your spine?

00:18:46.920 --> 00:18:50.420 align:middle line:84%
What are your body mechanics
as you go about being active?

00:18:50.420 --> 00:18:53.900 align:middle line:84%
And that's key,
because we all know

00:18:53.900 --> 00:18:56.480 align:middle line:84%
of people who have
injured themselves

00:18:56.480 --> 00:19:01.350 align:middle line:84%
while being active in sports
or just tying their shoelaces.

00:19:01.350 --> 00:19:06.830 align:middle line:84%
So just saying be active without
any further specifications,

00:19:06.830 --> 00:19:10.530 align:middle line:84%
we know, doesn't always
land a good result.

00:19:10.530 --> 00:19:13.980 align:middle line:84%
But active plus with
good posture is fabulous.

00:19:13.980 --> 00:19:14.780 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:19:14.780 --> 00:19:16.550 align:middle line:84%
The right kind of
active goes a long way.

00:19:16.550 --> 00:19:16.950 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:19:16.950 --> 00:19:17.750 align:middle line:90%
>> Right?

00:19:17.750 --> 00:19:21.110 align:middle line:84%
So what is your relationship
with other modalities,

00:19:21.110 --> 00:19:24.680 align:middle line:84%
other disciplines,
chiropractic, acupuncture,

00:19:24.680 --> 00:19:26.510 align:middle line:90%
physical therapists, et cetera.

00:19:26.510 --> 00:19:28.310 align:middle line:90%
What-- osteopathy.

00:19:28.310 --> 00:19:30.860 align:middle line:90%
What is the interaction there?

00:19:30.860 --> 00:19:35.600 align:middle line:84%
>> So I think collaboration
works particularly well,

00:19:35.600 --> 00:19:39.110 align:middle line:84%
because these are highly skilled
people who have been trained

00:19:39.110 --> 00:19:46.130 align:middle line:84%
for years and can do wonders
for inflammations or all sorts

00:19:46.130 --> 00:19:47.550 align:middle line:90%
of things.

00:19:47.550 --> 00:19:49.610 align:middle line:84%
There's a missing
piece, which is what

00:19:49.610 --> 00:19:51.360 align:middle line:90%
we try to bring to the table.

00:19:51.360 --> 00:19:54.440 align:middle line:84%
Which is like after you've had
your adjustment or your surgery

00:19:54.440 --> 00:19:58.190 align:middle line:84%
or your injection, what are
you doing when you go home?

00:19:58.190 --> 00:19:59.060 align:middle line:90%
How are you bending?

00:19:59.060 --> 00:19:59.970 align:middle line:90%
How are you sitting?

00:19:59.970 --> 00:20:04.690 align:middle line:84%
So we help people do
their part, and that

00:20:04.690 --> 00:20:07.180 align:middle line:84%
makes all of these
other interventions

00:20:07.180 --> 00:20:09.790 align:middle line:84%
so much more effective,
holds so much better.

00:20:09.790 --> 00:20:10.760 align:middle line:90%
>> Sustainable--

00:20:10.760 --> 00:20:11.130 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:20:11.130 --> 00:20:12.005 align:middle line:90%
>> --and integrative.

00:20:12.005 --> 00:20:16.180 align:middle line:84%
>> And so I think collaboration
is the right way to go.

00:20:16.180 --> 00:20:18.880 align:middle line:84%
The people who have
been the most receptive

00:20:18.880 --> 00:20:22.090 align:middle line:84%
have been the primary care
physicians, because they

00:20:22.090 --> 00:20:25.570 align:middle line:84%
are the ones who are facing
complaining patients who

00:20:25.570 --> 00:20:28.570 align:middle line:84%
have back problems, get
sent someplace, come back

00:20:28.570 --> 00:20:30.010 align:middle line:90%
with the same problem.

00:20:30.010 --> 00:20:34.360 align:middle line:84%
And we know from the research
and we know from our--

00:20:34.360 --> 00:20:36.490 align:middle line:84%
most people's experience
that most things

00:20:36.490 --> 00:20:39.040 align:middle line:84%
don't work very well or
they don't hold very well.

00:20:39.040 --> 00:20:41.727 align:middle line:84%
People keep coming back
with the same problems.

00:20:41.727 --> 00:20:42.810 align:middle line:90%
And so they appreciate it.

00:20:42.810 --> 00:20:45.490 align:middle line:84%
>> And the standard primary care
physician wasn't really trained

00:20:45.490 --> 00:20:47.000 align:middle line:84%
in biomechanics and
prevention and--

00:20:47.000 --> 00:20:47.800 align:middle line:90%
>> Correct

00:20:47.800 --> 00:20:48.580 align:middle line:90%
>> --those kinds of things.

00:20:48.580 --> 00:20:49.170 align:middle line:90%
>> So there is no turf--

00:20:49.170 --> 00:20:50.510 align:middle line:84%
>> They're a totally
different discipline.

00:20:50.510 --> 00:20:50.770 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:20:50.770 --> 00:20:53.080 align:middle line:84%
>> So they're thrilled
to have you on the scene,

00:20:53.080 --> 00:20:54.830 align:middle line:90%
showing everyone what to do--

00:20:54.830 --> 00:20:55.630 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:20:55.630 --> 00:20:59.200 align:middle line:84%
>> --instead of some of the
other more dramatic modalities

00:20:59.200 --> 00:21:02.170 align:middle line:84%
that would have to get suggested
in these circumstances.

00:21:02.170 --> 00:21:05.470 align:middle line:84%
How do you feel about lumbar
support, cervical pillows,

00:21:05.470 --> 00:21:10.830 align:middle line:84%
these kinds of supports as
people are sitting or sleeping,

00:21:10.830 --> 00:21:11.740 align:middle line:90%
et cetera?

00:21:11.740 --> 00:21:14.620 align:middle line:84%
>> So, again, it depends what
sort of philosophy they are

00:21:14.620 --> 00:21:15.580 align:middle line:90%
informed by.

00:21:15.580 --> 00:21:17.560 align:middle line:84%
So if it's a lumbar
support pillow,

00:21:17.560 --> 00:21:21.490 align:middle line:84%
trying to create extra
lumbar curve where I think it

00:21:21.490 --> 00:21:23.790 align:middle line:84%
should be more
lengthened and flat,

00:21:23.790 --> 00:21:26.380 align:middle line:90%
and then I'm not so thrilled.

00:21:26.380 --> 00:21:30.820 align:middle line:84%
