00:28:52.680 --> 00:28:55.600 align:middle line:84%
And we have a video of
her demonstrating it here.

00:28:55.600 --> 00:28:58.270 align:middle line:84%
>> Now we're going to learn
another simple technique called

00:28:58.270 --> 00:29:00.070 align:middle line:90%
stretch lying.

00:29:00.070 --> 00:29:03.730 align:middle line:84%
Stretch lying will make
you sleep more comfortably.

00:29:03.730 --> 00:29:06.790 align:middle line:84%
Begin by bending your
knees and placing your feet

00:29:06.790 --> 00:29:10.150 align:middle line:90%
hip width apart on the bed.

00:29:10.150 --> 00:29:12.910 align:middle line:84%
Prop your upper body
onto your elbows,

00:29:12.910 --> 00:29:17.740 align:middle line:84%
and now dig your elbows in
and push towards your feet,

00:29:17.740 --> 00:29:19.060 align:middle line:90%
putting one vertebra down.

00:29:19.060 --> 00:29:21.340 align:middle line:84%
Now you don't want to
jut out your rib cage.

00:29:21.340 --> 00:29:23.710 align:middle line:84%
You want to put one
vertebra down at a time

00:29:23.710 --> 00:29:25.870 align:middle line:90%
and uncurl onto the bed.

00:29:25.870 --> 00:29:27.010 align:middle line:90%
That's great.

00:29:27.010 --> 00:29:30.280 align:middle line:84%
Now you bring your
hands behind your neck

00:29:30.280 --> 00:29:32.630 align:middle line:84%
and elongate the
back of your neck.

00:29:32.630 --> 00:29:35.890 align:middle line:84%
And you want to not jut
the chin up, but rather

00:29:35.890 --> 00:29:40.210 align:middle line:84%
leave the neck elongated
and the chin down.

00:29:40.210 --> 00:29:43.450 align:middle line:84%
And then move your
hands out of the way.

00:29:43.450 --> 00:29:46.930 align:middle line:84%
And keeping the traction that
you've created in your back,

00:29:46.930 --> 00:29:50.110 align:middle line:84%
you are going to slide
your shoulders down

00:29:50.110 --> 00:29:53.870 align:middle line:90%
towards your feet.

00:29:53.870 --> 00:29:54.860 align:middle line:90%
Great.

00:29:54.860 --> 00:29:58.100 align:middle line:84%
Now straighten out
the knees and let

00:29:58.100 --> 00:30:03.980 align:middle line:84%
the knees slightly externally
rotate and lay on the pillow.

00:30:03.980 --> 00:30:04.780 align:middle line:90%
Looks good.

00:30:04.780 --> 00:30:08.870 align:middle line:84%
Lucy, if you can bring the
pillow under your shoulders,

00:30:08.870 --> 00:30:11.030 align:middle line:84%
that would be
better because that

00:30:11.030 --> 00:30:15.020 align:middle line:84%
helps you curve
your ribcage forward

00:30:15.020 --> 00:30:17.630 align:middle line:90%
and elongate your low back.

00:30:17.630 --> 00:30:20.780 align:middle line:84%
Do this for only five
minutes of the night,

00:30:20.780 --> 00:30:22.940 align:middle line:84%
but you may be surprised
that you stay there

00:30:22.940 --> 00:30:26.270 align:middle line:84%
for a longer period because
your body is so comfortable.

00:30:26.270 --> 00:30:28.910 align:middle line:84%
Many people tell me they
wake up in the same position

00:30:28.910 --> 00:30:31.097 align:middle line:84%
that they went to sleep
in, and they're shocked.

00:30:31.097 --> 00:30:33.680 align:middle line:84%
>> Who'd have thought we have
to be instructed so much on just

00:30:33.680 --> 00:30:34.730 align:middle line:90%
