00:36:31.050 --> 00:36:35.730 align:middle line:84%
But I did in some point
take our foundation's course

00:36:35.730 --> 00:36:37.290 align:middle line:84%
and learn in a
formal way what it

00:36:37.290 --> 00:36:40.560 align:middle line:84%
meant to have healthy
posture habits

00:36:40.560 --> 00:36:42.970 align:middle line:84%
and healthy
structural integrity.

00:36:42.970 --> 00:36:46.590 align:middle line:84%
And then went on to train
to be a Gokhale Method

00:36:46.590 --> 00:36:48.280 align:middle line:90%
teacher about eight years ago.

00:36:48.280 --> 00:36:50.220 align:middle line:90%
And ever since, I've been--

00:36:50.220 --> 00:36:56.100 align:middle line:84%
I started teaching alongside
my studying at Stanford.

00:36:56.100 --> 00:36:57.490 align:middle line:90%
I was a computer science major.

00:36:57.490 --> 00:36:59.340 align:middle line:84%
And in summer as
an in-between, I

00:36:59.340 --> 00:37:01.080 align:middle line:84%
did a little bit of
teaching on the side.

00:37:01.080 --> 00:37:05.330 align:middle line:84%
And two years ago, I
formally joined full time.

00:37:05.330 --> 00:37:08.750 align:middle line:84%
>> Esther, in what other ways
do people benefit from improving

00:37:08.750 --> 00:37:10.880 align:middle line:90%
their posture?

00:37:10.880 --> 00:37:16.780 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, they improve all of
their joints and muscle health.

00:37:16.780 --> 00:37:20.800 align:middle line:84%
That's the nuts and bolts
of the obvious ways.

00:37:20.800 --> 00:37:24.490 align:middle line:84%
But they also report that
they're sleeping better,

00:37:24.490 --> 00:37:25.780 align:middle line:90%
that they breathe better.

00:37:25.780 --> 00:37:29.980 align:middle line:84%
Their digestion improves
because their organs now

00:37:29.980 --> 00:37:33.700 align:middle line:84%
have more room, better
orientation, better blood

00:37:33.700 --> 00:37:36.730 align:middle line:90%
supply, better nerve supply.

00:37:36.730 --> 00:37:40.750 align:middle line:84%
So they get results that
they weren't expecting.

00:37:40.750 --> 00:37:42.970 align:middle line:84%
And then there's the
whole psychological piece

00:37:42.970 --> 00:37:44.740 align:middle line:90%
that people feel more confident.

00:37:44.740 --> 00:37:48.950 align:middle line:84%
Other people are responding
to them differently.

00:37:48.950 --> 00:37:56.200 align:middle line:84%
So there's a whole layered
series of benefits.

00:37:56.200 --> 00:37:59.540 align:middle line:84%
>> And is there data supporting
the work that you're doing?

00:37:59.540 --> 00:38:02.950 align:middle line:84%
>> So we've done
in-house studies,

00:38:02.950 --> 00:38:07.000 align:middle line:84%
and we expected the result that
people are improving pretty

00:38:07.000 --> 00:38:10.600 align:middle line:84%
dramatically from the beginning
to the end of the course.

00:38:10.600 --> 00:38:15.210 align:middle line:84%
Our study followed
these students one month

00:38:15.210 --> 00:38:16.200 align:middle line:90%
beyond the course.

00:38:16.200 --> 00:38:20.400 align:middle line:84%
And I wasn't sure if they would
forget more or integrate more,

00:38:20.400 --> 00:38:22.590 align:middle line:84%
and it turns out
they keep improving.

00:38:22.590 --> 00:38:27.090 align:middle line:84%
So integrating is more important
than forgetting, it turns out.

00:38:27.090 --> 00:38:33.660 align:middle line:84%
There's a crowdsourcing website
called healthoutcome.org,

00:38:33.660 --> 00:38:37.710 align:middle line:84%
and we are the number
one rated intervention

00:38:37.710 --> 00:38:39.390 align:middle line:90%
for lower back pain.

00:38:39.390 --> 00:38:42.840 align:middle line:84%
And this is a matter of
great satisfaction and pride,

00:38:42.840 --> 00:38:45.090 align:middle line:90%
because this is not our website.

00:38:45.090 --> 00:38:49.410 align:middle line:10%
This is a third party website,
having nothing to do with us,

00:38:49.410 --> 00:38:52.830 align:middle line:10%
and actually teaching
something competitive.

00:38:52.830 --> 00:38:56.610 align:middle line:10%
And we just rate
head and shoulders

00:38:56.610 --> 00:39:01.290 align:middle line:10%
above everything else, so
that was delightful to see.

00:39:01.290 --> 00:39:05.070 align:middle line:84%
And now there are an increasing
number of research studies

00:39:05.070 --> 00:39:08.520 align:middle line:84%
